Claude SDK in main.js: You will require and instantiate the Claude SDK in your main process. This SDK will be the source of the AI's commands.

SDK Event Handling: The SDK will likely provide events (e.g., when the AI decides on an action). Your main.js code will listen for these events.

IPC Main -> Renderer: When your main.js code receives an action event from the SDK, it will forward the command to the renderer using the same ai-cursor-command IPC channel as before.

Renderer Execution: The renderer code remains unchanged. It still listens for ai-cursor-command and handles the visual cursor animation and typing simulation within the <webview>.

## The Code: SDK Integration
You only need to change main.js. The files preload.js, renderer/app.js, index.html, and your CSS file with the #ai-cursor style are all correct and do not need any modifications.

main.js - Replace the Server with the SDK
We will remove the http server and create a new function to initialize the Claude SDK.

Note: Since I don't have access to the specific Claude Code SDK, I'm providing a realistic example based on how modern SDKs typically work. You will need to adjust the package name and method calls to match the SDK's actual documentation.

JavaScript

// In main.js

// Remove or comment out the 'http' requirement
// const http = require('http');

// ** NEW: Hypothetical Claude Code SDK Integration **
// You will need to install the actual SDK, e.g., via 'npm install @claude/code-sdk'
// and adjust the name here.
const { ClaudeSDK } = require('@claude/code-sdk'); // This is a placeholder name

/**
 * Initializes the Claude SDK and sets up listeners for AI actions.
 * @param {SlitherChromeContainer} appInstance - The main instance of your application.
 */
function setupClaudeSDK(appInstance) {
    // 1. Instantiate the SDK with your credentials
    const claude = new ClaudeSDK({
        apiKey: process.env.CLAUDE_API_KEY, // It's best practice to use environment variables
        // ... other SDK-specific options
    });

    // 2. Set up a listener for when the AI wants to perform an action
    claude.on('action', (action) => {
        console.log('ðŸ¤– Received action from Claude SDK:', action);

        // 3. Forward the action to the renderer for execution, just like before
        if (appInstance.mainWindow && !appInstance.mainWindow.isDestroyed()) {
            appInstance.mainWindow.webContents.send('ai-cursor-command', action);
        }
    });

    // 4. Connect or start the SDK session
    claude.connect().then(() => {
        console.log('âœ… Claude SDK connected and ready.');
    }).catch(err => {
        console.error('âŒ Failed to connect Claude SDK:', err);
    });
}

